# Apartment Room Rules WebsiteThis is a multilingual website for managing and sharing the rules of your apartment with your friends. It supports English, Kurdish, and Arabic, and is fully responsive and printable.## Features- Beautiful welcome section with all roommates' names- Rules in English, Kurdish, and Arabic (switchable)- Print or save rules as PDF- Responsive design for mobile and desktop- Animated footer with credits and contact info## How to Use1. **Open the Website**   - Open `index.sherwan.html` in your browser.2. **Switch Languages**   - Use the language buttons at the top to view rules in English, Kurdish, or Arabic.3. **Print or Save as PDF**   - Click the "??? Print / Save as PDF" button to print or save the rules.## How to PublishYou can publish your website for free using [GitHub Pages](https://pages.github.com/) or [Netlify](https://www.netlify.com/):### GitHub Pages1. Create a GitHub account if you don't have one.2. Create a new repository (e.g., `apartment-rules`).3. Upload your `index.sherwan.html` file to the repository.4. Go to repository **Settings** > **Pages**.5. Under "Source", select the branch (usually `main`) and `/root` folder.6. Your website will be published at `https://yourusername.github.io/apartment-rules/`.### Netlify1. Go to [Netlify](https://www.netlify.com/) and sign up.2. Click "Add new site" > "Import an existing project".3. Connect your GitHub repository or drag and drop your `index.sherwan.html` file.4. Netlify will give you a live link to your website.---**If you want to use a different name for your HTML file, rename it to `index.html` before publishing.**---## CreditsWebsite design and rules by Zhiyar, Ramyar, and friends.---